Place 1¼ cups water and a pinch of @salt{pinch} in a small #pot{} and bring to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Drain and rinse @kidney beans{13.4%ounce}. Core and seed @poblano pepper{1}, then cut into ½-inch squares. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Slice @jalapeño{1} into thin rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Finely dice @dried chorizo{3%ounce}. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}(finely chopped).

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{¾%cup} to #pot{}. Lower heat, reduce to a gentle simmer, and cover. Let cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from heat and let steam, covered, until rest of meal is ready.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and 1 1/2 tsp @enchilada spice blend{1%tablespoon} (save the rest of the spice for the next step). Cook, breaking up meat into small pieces, until browned and cooked through, about ~{6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove beef from pan.

Toss a drizzle of oil, onion, scallion whites, and poblano into the same pan. Toss in chorizo and remaining enchilada spice. Cook, tossing, until onion and poblano are softened, about ~{4%minutes}. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, beans, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, and ½ cup water. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to a simmer. Stir in beef. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

If chili is too thick, add a splash more water. Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Measure out 2 cups rice and divide between #bowls{}. Set aside a quarter of the chili for lunch, then add rest to bowls. Top with 2 TBSP @sour cream{6%tablespoon} and ¼ cup @cheddar cheese{1%cup}. Garnish with scallion greens and as much jalapeño as you like. Sprinkle with half the cilantro. Serve.

== Lunch Burrito ==

When you're ready to pack your lunch, slice @roma tomato{1} into thin rounds. Spread @flour tortillas{2} with remaining sour cream and sprinkle with remaining cheddar. Divide tomato, reserved chili, any remaining jalapeño, remaining rice, and remaining cilantro between tortillas. Roll into burritos and place in #reusable containers{}. Keep refrigerated. Reheat in #microwave{} before enjoying.

> The Lunch Burrito transforms leftovers into a delicious next-day meal. The spices have time to rest and intensify!